    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5017/11–2045: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Certain American
                            Republics</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="28" xml:id="d241fn28">Sent to the diplomatic representatives in the
                        American Republics except Argentina, Bolivia, Chile, Panama, Paraguay, and
                        Uruguay.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-20">November 20,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following decision on coffee ceiling prices announced Nov. 17 by OWMR<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d241fn29">Office of War Mobilization and Reconversion.</note> after
                    extensive consultation top levels <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Subsidy 3 cents per pound to be paid US importers on maximum 6 million
                            bags green coffee shipped from foreign ports between Nov. 19, 1945 and
                            March 31, 1946 for consumption in US. Importers to participate in
                            subsidy in proportion to their WFO–63 import allocations and in
                            accordance with inventory regulations.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Effective Nov. 19, buying price ceilings wall be raised 3 cents per
                            pound on coffee eligible for subsidy only for duration of
                            subsidy.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>No ceiling price increase for green or roasted coffee in US.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>US stabilization policy and prospective world coffee supply situation basic
                    considerations in decision that increase or removal of ceilings requested by
                    producing countries cannot be granted.</p>
                <p>Full details follow by air.<note n="30" xml:id="d241fn30">Circular airgram,
                        November 30, 1945, 12:20 p.m., not printed, but see 10 <hi rend="italic"
                            >Federal Register</hi> 14450.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
